    <item>
      <title>Science Is an Error-Correcting Mechanism</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/science-is-an-error-correcting-mechanism/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 30 Apr 2021 16:57:29 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/science-is-an-error-correcting-mechanism/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/science-is-an-error-correcting-mechanism.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://nav.al/error&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://nav.al/error&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://nav.al/error&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;science-is-an-error-correcting-mechanism&#34;&gt;Science Is an Error-Correcting Mechanism&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apr 30 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;Where do good explanations come from?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There&amp;rsquo;s currently an obsession with &lt;strong&gt;induction&lt;/strong&gt;, the idea that you can predict the future from the past. You can say, &amp;ldquo;I saw one, then two, then three, then four, then five, so therefore next must be six, seven, eight, nine.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
